> When sliced thinly, raw zucchini can provide all the fresh crispness of a salad
> while also holding the fresh flavors of a citrus marinade. Which is why it's
> perfect for this recipe, bringing a cool contrast to the chili-accented shrimp
> and warm jasmine rice. It even gets an additional boost from an infused basil
> olive oil, which creates a wave of herby aromatics.

Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites
from greens. Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add
scallion whites and cook until just softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with
@salt{}.

Pour in @water{3/4%cup} and bring to a boil.

Once water boils, add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} to #pot{} and stir to combine.
Cover, lower heat, and reduce to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender,
~{12-15%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to use.

Meanwhile, zest 1 tsp zest from @lemon{1}, then cut into quarters. Trim ends
from @zucchini{1}. Working over a #large bowl{}, shave zucchini lengthwise into
thin ribbons using a #peeler{}, rotating as you go. Stop once you get to the
seedy core; discard core.

Toss zucchini with @basil oil{5%tsp} and half the lemon zest. Season with plenty
of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Squeeze in juice from 1 lemon quarter and toss to
coat. Set aside. Rinse @shrimp{10%oz}, then pat dry with #paper towels{}
and season all over with plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} and @butter{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add shrimp and season with
@chili flakes{1%tsp} (to taste—start with ¼ tsp and add more from there).
Cook, tossing, until pink and firm, ~{3-5%minutes}.

While shrimp cook, place another @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}.
Microwave until melted, about ~{1%minute}. Squeeze in juice from another lemon
quarter. Stir, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Divide between
#bowls{}. Shake off any excess marinade from zucchini, then arrange ribbons
on top of rice. Place shrimp on top, then drizzle with lemon butter. Garnish
with scallion greens, remaining lemon zest, and additional chili flakes
(to taste). Serve with remaining lemon quarters.